Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place turkey wings and onion in a casserole dish; sprinkle seasoned salt, poultry seasoning, black pepper, and garlic on both sides of each wing. Pour 1/2 cup water into the casserole dish. Cover casserole dish. Bake in the preheated oven until browned, 1 hour. Stir cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup water together in a bowl; pour over turkey wings into casserole dish and return to oven, uncovered. Continue baking until brown and tender, 1 hour.